    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. so if we're doing FOB, and something goes wrong while the container is being hoisted or if it gets damaged during the loading process in Ningbo, that's our problem, not the supplier's? what about insurance specifically—do we need to take out a separate policy for that if we're using FOB?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, if using FOB, any damage during the loading process in Ningbo is your responsibility because the risk has transferred to you at that point. Since the seller's obligation ends when the goods are loaded onto the ship, you absolutely need to arrange and purchase your own insurance policy. This insurance must cover you from the point where you took over the risk in Ningbo all the way to Rotterdam to protect your investment.",
      "source": "target",
